WEBVTT

00:06.180 --> 00:08.573
You need to get Gertrude's death
certificate from City Hall,

00:08.617 --> 00:11.228
and you need to do it fast.I found it. Ha!

00:11.315 --> 00:14.536
You know, I've actually been
in the newspaper before.

00:14.623 --> 00:16.886
♪♪

00:16.973 --> 00:18.931
You caused a city-wide
power outage.

00:19.019 --> 00:21.151
You have to take responsibility
for something, Kevin.

00:21.238 --> 00:23.893
It's the security footage
from Vermont, right?

00:23.980 --> 00:25.068
I'm just gonna say it.

00:25.112 --> 00:26.722
Do you want to
move in with me?

00:26.809 --> 00:29.029
You won't live here
anymore.Neither will you.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.856
I do want to help you.

00:30.943 --> 00:33.076
♪♪

00:33.120 --> 00:35.383
[Crying]
Oh. Oh.

00:41.563 --> 00:43.782
[Yawning]

00:43.869 --> 00:45.784
That's enough!

00:45.871 --> 00:47.482
Hey, hey!
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:47.569 --> 00:49.223
Dad, no one should
see this paper!

00:49.310 --> 00:51.181
It's a disgrace and no one
should ever read it!

00:51.268 --> 00:53.879
That's not
the only copy, son!

00:53.966 --> 00:56.404
Gah!

00:56.491 --> 00:59.059
It would have been
symbolic!

00:59.146 --> 01:00.538
What'd they do to you?

01:00.625 --> 01:02.105
They minted someone else

01:02.192 --> 01:04.977
as the town's biggest
local celebrity.

01:05.065 --> 01:08.242
"The New Worcester Wild Dude."
Oof.

01:08.329 --> 01:11.506
And they say that
he's cuter than me!

01:11.593 --> 01:13.247
Well, that's not
your fault, son.

01:13.334 --> 01:14.378
He's a horse.

01:14.465 --> 01:16.640
Not even
a miniature, Dad!

01:16.728 --> 01:19.731
He's a regular, big-boy-sized
racehorse.

01:19.818 --> 01:22.604
His name is
"Straw Man's Argument".

01:22.646 --> 01:24.562
Ha-ha!
That's pretty cute.

01:24.649 --> 01:26.608
Dad, I've seen
your girlfriend.

01:26.651 --> 01:29.306
Your cute barometer
ain't workin'.

01:29.350 --> 01:31.569
And good morning
to you, Kevin.

01:31.656 --> 01:33.136
Oh, hey!

01:33.223 --> 01:36.531
And this article was written
by that hack of a reporter

01:36.618 --> 01:39.098
who did that hit job
of an interview of me.

01:39.186 --> 01:41.622
That's it.
This will not stand.

01:41.710 --> 01:46.454
Reporter Kelly McDunnaugh
has got to be stopped.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.282
What are you gonna do?

01:48.369 --> 01:49.935
Justice, Dad.

01:50.021 --> 01:51.850
Simple justice.

01:51.937 --> 01:58.509
♪♪

01:58.596 --> 02:05.212
♪♪

02:05.299 --> 02:09.651
♪♪

02:09.693 --> 02:12.175
[Sighs]

02:12.219 --> 02:15.787
[Whirring]

02:15.874 --> 02:18.616
[Studio audience laughing]

02:20.401 --> 02:23.186
♪

02:23.230 --> 02:26.189
[Yawning]

02:26.276 --> 02:27.538
Whoa!

02:27.625 --> 02:35.677
[Studio audience laughing]

02:35.720 --> 02:36.939
Other shoe!

02:37.026 --> 02:38.853
[Studio audience laughing]

02:44.076 --> 02:47.428
I have got to be to work
by 8:55 this morning.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.952
Alexa, what time is it?

02:49.995 --> 02:52.346
It's 8:55 A.M.
Gah!

02:52.433 --> 02:54.216
Since when do you care
about being late?

02:54.304 --> 02:56.263
Mr. Harrison said that if I keep
showing up late,

02:56.305 --> 02:59.788
we're gonna have to discuss
"my future at the company."

02:59.875 --> 03:02.617
Ah.
I hate discussions.

03:02.704 --> 03:04.662
That's why I never gave you
the sex talk.

03:04.749 --> 03:08.057
Just one condom
and a heartfelt "good luck."

03:08.144 --> 03:10.451
I have got to find a way
to get to work faster.

03:10.538 --> 03:14.237
Alexa, set Kevin's work
alarm for six minutes earlier.

03:14.281 --> 03:18.546
Now set for 10:54 A.M.

03:18.633 --> 03:21.201
You have your work alarm
set for 11:00?

03:21.288 --> 03:24.508
Do I look like a man
who lives by a clock?

03:24.595 --> 03:28.469
Listen, what I need is
your help to up my efficiency.

03:28.556 --> 03:30.471
You see, there's this one
intersection on the way to work

03:30.558 --> 03:34.301
with this stop sign
that I've decided is my nemesis.

03:34.388 --> 03:36.390
We've just gotta find
a shortcut.

03:36.477 --> 03:38.783
Aren't you late?Oh, God, yes!

03:38.870 --> 03:41.873
[Studio audience laughing]

03:41.960 --> 03:42.787
Breakfast.

03:42.874 --> 03:47.444
[Studio audience laughing]

03:47.531 --> 03:51.013
♪♪

03:51.100 --> 03:54.059
So, where does Chuck
think you are?

03:54.146 --> 03:57.019
Uh, that would require
Chuck thinking about me.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.761
Oh.
Right.

04:01.763 --> 04:06.115
So, this is where you stayed
before you moved back in?

04:06.158 --> 04:07.072
Yep.

04:07.116 --> 04:11.163
My big three-day
rebellion.

04:11.251 --> 04:13.470
Though I guess
you sort of count.

04:13.514 --> 04:17.039
Yeah -- you can use me
to rebel all you want.

04:18.867 --> 04:22.087
Hey, what are you doin'
Friday night?

04:22.174 --> 04:23.045
Workin'.

04:23.088 --> 04:24.916
Wanna hit up the Seas after?

04:25.003 --> 04:27.179
I get free popcorn.

04:27.267 --> 04:29.573
I'm a regular.

04:29.660 --> 04:33.621
Everyone gets free popcorn,
sweets.

04:33.707 --> 04:36.624
And I think you and me
are more of a...

04:36.711 --> 04:40.671
just-in-this-room
sorta thing.

04:40.715 --> 04:43.152
Oh -- yeah!
Yeah, sure.

04:43.239 --> 04:46.721
No, I --
Like I said, I like the room.

04:48.723 --> 04:50.986
Well, I should
get going.

04:53.510 --> 04:55.947
Yeah.

04:56.034 --> 04:57.471
Me, too.

04:57.558 --> 05:04.347
♪♪

05:04.434 --> 05:06.567
Allison: I don't know.
I'm not really sure yet.

05:06.654 --> 05:09.657
So, you're still mulling
how you're going to --

05:09.744 --> 05:11.311
to fake your own death.

05:11.398 --> 05:13.138
I was thinking maybe I would
make it look

05:13.225 --> 05:15.358
like a --
a hiking accident.

05:15.402 --> 05:19.231
Or maybe drive Kevin's car
off a bridge.

05:19.275 --> 05:21.408
"Maybe drive Kevin's car
off a bridge"?!

05:21.451 --> 05:26.021
Okay, like I said,
I haven't figured it out yet.

05:26.108 --> 05:29.894
And you're okay with
all this?

05:29.938 --> 05:31.505
The other night,
the blackout?

05:31.592 --> 05:32.767
Oh.

05:32.854 --> 05:33.898
That was, uh --

05:33.985 --> 05:35.378
That was a weird moment.

05:35.465 --> 05:36.901
I --
Sorry.

05:36.945 --> 05:39.643
No, you don't
have to be sorry.

05:39.730 --> 05:43.081
So, what else is next?
Uh, ID?

05:43.125 --> 05:47.390
Uh, well, the death certificate
got me Gertrude's Social,

05:47.477 --> 05:50.045
and with that, I was able
to get her birth certificate,

05:50.132 --> 05:54.136
and Billy made me all this
fake mail, so I can --

05:54.223 --> 05:57.139
I can go
to the RMV whenever.

05:57.226 --> 05:58.488
But you haven't.

05:58.575 --> 06:01.012
Are you dying
to go to the RMV?

06:01.099 --> 06:02.666
Allie, you're stalling.I'm not!

06:02.753 --> 06:04.233
I have a lot of things
I need to do.

06:04.320 --> 06:06.757
I need ID, I need to figure
out money --

06:06.844 --> 06:09.238
That's not a real problem, you
could always find more money.

06:09.325 --> 06:11.849
Okay, just don't --
don't say things like that.

06:11.936 --> 06:12.937
I just --

06:13.024 --> 06:14.678
I thought you were
in trouble,

06:14.765 --> 06:17.942
that you had to leave,
that you were desperate and --

06:18.029 --> 06:19.422
Well, I am!
I am,

06:19.509 --> 06:21.946
but I want to actually
think about things

06:21.990 --> 06:24.601
before I just go ahead
and dive into --

06:24.645 --> 06:26.821
[Crashing]

06:26.908 --> 06:32.217
[Horn blaring]

06:32.304 --> 06:33.305
[Knocking at door]

06:33.393 --> 06:38.920
♪♪

06:38.963 --> 06:40.095
Hi.

06:40.138 --> 06:42.358
Whoa.I know.

06:43.881 --> 06:45.492
What happened?

06:45.579 --> 06:48.364
Uh, I got into a car accident
with Sam.

06:48.451 --> 06:50.801
I could've sworn that there was
a stop sign, at --

06:50.888 --> 06:52.542
at Primrose and Vine.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.457
Well, that's like
two miles away.

06:54.501 --> 06:55.806
Did you walk here?!

06:55.850 --> 06:57.417
Yeah, but I-I went by
the reservoir,

06:57.460 --> 06:59.114
so it was actually kinda nice.

06:59.201 --> 07:01.116
Where's Sam?
Why did he let you do that?

07:01.203 --> 07:02.900
Oh, no, he's fine.
He's fine.

07:02.987 --> 07:05.250
I just had to leave befe
the EMTs got there.

07:05.337 --> 07:07.427
They'd take me to
the hospital

07:07.514 --> 07:09.167
and then Jenn and Kevin wd
have all these questions, so --

07:09.254 --> 07:11.474
You don't know that they would
have taken you to the hospital.

07:11.561 --> 07:13.781
I do.I do.

07:13.868 --> 07:16.479
Uh...

07:16.566 --> 07:19.351
My --
My shoulder popped out.

07:19.439 --> 07:24.966
♪♪

07:25.053 --> 07:27.447
I just feel like I don't know
how to have any fun.

07:27.534 --> 07:30.754
Do you know
how to have fun?

07:30.841 --> 07:35.193
Uh, fun is for people
with disposable income.

07:35.237 --> 07:37.935
Yeah, and I don't have
disposable income?

07:38.022 --> 07:39.284
That's never stopped him.

07:39.371 --> 07:42.462
That is actually the one --

07:42.549 --> 07:47.683
the one thing that I kinda
maybe admire about him.

07:47.771 --> 07:49.164
Okay.

07:49.251 --> 07:52.558
Maybe you stop drinking now.

07:52.646 --> 07:56.258
I mean, I've never gambled,
I've never been in a fight.

07:56.345 --> 07:59.261
Well, I got poker chips,
and I punch real good.

07:59.348 --> 08:00.828
Ask Neil.
Let's go.

08:00.915 --> 08:03.178
I just can't die
without having any fun,

08:03.221 --> 08:06.398
and it -- I could --
I could.

08:06.442 --> 08:10.490
I had a near-death
experience today.

08:10.577 --> 08:13.493
My shoulder popped out.

08:13.580 --> 08:15.016
Feel it.

08:15.059 --> 08:16.017
Gross.
No way.

08:16.104 --> 08:17.366
If you're gonna be the one

08:17.453 --> 08:19.237
to pop it back in,
you have to --

08:19.324 --> 08:20.151
No!
Gross.

08:20.238 --> 08:21.718
Okay, just -- Hey.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.372
Let's follow the instructions.

08:23.459 --> 08:25.505
Mm.

08:25.548 --> 08:28.159
This says --
Alright.

08:28.246 --> 08:30.553
You gotta hold the wrist
of the injured arm,

08:30.640 --> 08:31.989
then I gotta pull straight
and forward --

08:32.076 --> 08:34.034
Okay, okay!
But you have to --

08:34.078 --> 08:35.905
You have to go fast.

08:35.993 --> 08:37.212
Well, then, no.

08:37.299 --> 08:39.082
No.
I'm not ready.

08:39.169 --> 08:41.172
Alright.

08:41.259 --> 08:42.609
Let me know when you're ready.

08:42.696 --> 08:44.567
Okay.

08:44.654 --> 08:46.395
I thought
you were movin'.

08:46.482 --> 08:47.701
I am.

08:47.788 --> 08:49.354
Well, why aren't
you packed?

08:49.441 --> 08:51.792
Well...

08:51.879 --> 08:53.358
So what?
I'm moving soon.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.578
Who likes to pack?

08:55.665 --> 08:57.058
I do.

08:57.145 --> 08:58.929
I love organizing.

08:59.016 --> 09:01.366
I have this --
Ah!

09:01.453 --> 09:04.500
[Groaning]

09:04.587 --> 09:07.764
There.

09:07.808 --> 09:09.766
That was kinda fun.

09:09.853 --> 09:13.509
Does it feel better?No!

09:13.596 --> 09:16.251
No, it still hurts,
but it's different.

09:16.294 --> 09:17.731
Hey.

09:17.818 --> 09:19.602
What are you gonna tell Kevin
when he notices

09:19.646 --> 09:22.126
you're waiting on him
hand and foot...

09:22.170 --> 09:25.608
with one less hand?

09:25.695 --> 09:30.134
Maybe now is the opportunity
to finally have some fun.

09:30.221 --> 09:37.489
♪♪

09:37.577 --> 09:44.888
♪♪

09:44.975 --> 09:48.065
Oh.
[Rueful laughter]

09:48.152 --> 09:49.676
Fuck you.

09:54.376 --> 10:01.775
♪

10:01.862 --> 10:02.993
I woke up.

10:03.037 --> 10:04.952
Another win.

10:05.039 --> 10:06.823
Depends on who you ask.

10:06.910 --> 10:09.304
[Bag crunches]

10:09.391 --> 10:12.307
Dad, is your butt crunching?

10:12.394 --> 10:14.352
[Studio audience laughing]

10:14.439 --> 10:17.573
This couch
is covered in crumbs.

10:17.660 --> 10:20.184
Now that you mention it,
the house is starting to look

10:20.228 --> 10:22.752
a lot like that
old condom in my wallet.

10:22.839 --> 10:25.102
[Studio audience laughing]

10:25.189 --> 10:26.930
Defective?

10:27.017 --> 10:28.323
Rough around the edges.

10:28.410 --> 10:30.194
[Studio audience laughing]

10:30.281 --> 10:32.457
Hey, uh, Allison, the house
is starting to look

10:32.544 --> 10:34.938
a little...
disgusting.

10:35.025 --> 10:36.636
When are you gonna
clean next?

10:36.723 --> 10:39.900
Well, I am on strike
from house cleaning,

10:39.987 --> 10:41.815
because I clean all day
long at the diner,

10:41.902 --> 10:43.512
and I don't want to do it
when I get home,

10:43.599 --> 10:45.035
so I am on strike.

10:45.122 --> 10:46.994
[Studio audience laughing]

10:47.081 --> 10:49.170
I'm just taking a page
out of your book, Kev.

10:49.257 --> 10:51.607
You always said that after
work is "me" time.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.435
Can you even go on strike?

10:53.522 --> 10:55.176
You're not in a union.

10:55.263 --> 10:56.786
If only.[Scoffs]

10:56.873 --> 10:59.267
[Studio audience laughing]

11:02.705 --> 11:06.013
Sam at the diner's
really working her to the bone.

11:06.100 --> 11:08.711
She's so distracted, she's
forgetting about her work here,

11:08.755 --> 11:11.192
which I know
she secretly enjoys.

11:11.279 --> 11:12.715
[Studio audience laughing]

11:12.802 --> 11:16.284
That's it, I gotta take care of
this right now.

11:16.371 --> 11:18.329
Ooh!
A full chip.

11:18.373 --> 11:20.723
Ah!
Lucky.

11:20.810 --> 11:23.813
[Playful sitcom music]

11:23.900 --> 11:27.599
[Dramatic music]

11:27.687 --> 11:35.433
♪♪

11:35.520 --> 11:43.093
♪♪

11:43.180 --> 11:45.269
[Footsteps approach]

11:45.356 --> 11:49.578
♪♪

11:49.621 --> 11:51.319
[Exhales]

11:55.323 --> 11:57.194
You, uh --
You slept well.

11:57.281 --> 12:00.284
Yeah.
Finally.

12:00.371 --> 12:03.897
First real pain meds
I've had in eight years.

12:06.290 --> 12:08.423
It's just Tylenol
with Codeine.

12:11.208 --> 12:12.862
Must've knocked you out
pretty good to sleep

12:12.949 --> 12:15.256
through what went on here
last hour.

12:15.343 --> 12:19.129
You have a bunch of bikers
over or something?

12:19.216 --> 12:21.001
No.

12:21.088 --> 12:23.960
No, just Allison's husband.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.440
But he's loud all
on his own.

12:25.527 --> 12:27.050
Kevin?

12:27.137 --> 12:29.226
Kevin was here?

12:29.313 --> 12:30.445
Mm-hmm.

12:30.488 --> 12:31.925
Why?

12:32.012 --> 12:33.622
He says that you are

12:33.709 --> 12:36.103
working Allison
too hard.

12:36.190 --> 12:38.540
Seems to think that you're
keeping the diner open

12:38.627 --> 12:41.325
to avoid
your disastrous home life.

12:41.412 --> 12:45.503
Okay, I did not say
anything about -- what --

12:45.590 --> 12:48.463
He came by the diner last week
and he saw me sleeping --

12:48.550 --> 12:51.596
He also said that since Allison
started at the diner,

12:51.683 --> 12:54.948
she's been working until
midnight at least once a week.

12:56.776 --> 12:59.996
The diner isn't open
until midnight.

13:00.040 --> 13:03.086
Now, I was under the impression
that you were at

13:03.173 --> 13:05.262
AA meetings those nights,

13:05.349 --> 13:07.134
and, uh --
and I told him that,

13:07.221 --> 13:10.877
and that I saw Allison
once there, too.

13:10.964 --> 13:14.315
Jenn --And I re--
I really want to believe it,

13:14.402 --> 13:16.012
that you two were just --

13:16.099 --> 13:19.320
you were going to
AA meetings together.

13:19.407 --> 13:22.802
I don't think
Kevin bought it.

13:22.889 --> 13:24.020
And if he can't...

13:24.107 --> 13:34.074
♪♪

13:34.161 --> 13:35.815
We should talk.

13:37.991 --> 13:40.341
Do we have to?

13:40.428 --> 13:42.386
Yeah.

13:42.473 --> 13:44.171
We do.

13:46.826 --> 13:49.045
Does she hate me?

13:49.132 --> 13:50.351
Right now, she does.

13:50.438 --> 13:52.266
I'm right there with you.

13:52.353 --> 13:55.704
God, I'm sorry.

13:55.790 --> 13:57.793
Do you think I should call
her and apologize?

13:57.880 --> 13:59.839
No, no.
Definitely no.

14:02.450 --> 14:07.020
At least Kevin bought that
we were going to AA together.

14:07.107 --> 14:08.717
Thank God.

14:08.760 --> 14:10.153
Kind of.

14:10.240 --> 14:12.764
Well, he cornered me last night
and told me sobriety

14:12.852 --> 14:15.376
was the reason
I'm not fun anymore.

14:15.463 --> 14:18.292
Called it a
"reverse intervention."

14:18.379 --> 14:19.859
Jesus.

14:19.946 --> 14:24.559
It's scary how okay he can seem
after 10 car bombs.

14:24.602 --> 14:26.822
Still sounds better than my day.

14:26.909 --> 14:30.086
God, I'm sorry.

14:30.173 --> 14:32.175
I feel like
my near-death energy

14:32.262 --> 14:35.222
lasted 24 hours.

14:35.309 --> 14:38.225
Leave it to Kevin
to bring you back to reality.

14:38.268 --> 14:40.053
Yeah.

14:40.140 --> 14:41.663
But...
[Sighs]

14:41.750 --> 14:45.493
Jenn and I have been
struggling for so long.

14:45.580 --> 14:48.278
Even before
we moved back here.

14:48.365 --> 14:51.238
I feel like we could have
pretended forever,

14:51.281 --> 14:52.717
but now...

14:52.804 --> 14:56.417
Kevin blew up your life.
Welcome.

14:56.504 --> 15:00.160
The thing is,
I'm not sure I'm angry.

15:02.379 --> 15:05.600
Maybe it's my near-death energy
talking, but...

15:05.687 --> 15:06.906
I might a--

15:06.993 --> 15:11.084
I might actually
be grateful to him.

15:11.171 --> 15:13.434
Grateful?I know.

15:13.521 --> 15:15.088
It's scary, right?

15:15.175 --> 15:16.741
♪♪

15:16.828 --> 15:19.135
[Sighs]

15:19.222 --> 15:20.310
Yeah.

15:20.397 --> 15:26.316
♪♪

15:26.403 --> 15:27.665
Oh.

15:27.752 --> 15:29.232
Hello.

15:29.319 --> 15:30.625
Hey, what can
I get ya?

15:30.668 --> 15:33.019
[Sighs]
I am not sure yet.

15:33.106 --> 15:35.456
Ah.

15:35.543 --> 15:39.373
I haven't been in here
in a while.

15:39.460 --> 15:42.811
Not since
my husband's ad aired.

15:42.898 --> 15:46.423
You know --
"Wild Dude."

15:46.510 --> 15:48.817
[Groans]

15:48.860 --> 15:51.863
Hey, that's right!

15:51.951 --> 15:53.996
Man.

15:54.040 --> 15:56.259
You must laugh, like,
all the time

15:56.346 --> 15:58.435
with a guy like that
at home.

16:00.742 --> 16:03.179
Um, anyway, uh, I guess
I will get --

16:03.266 --> 16:05.486
Unh-uh. Hey, hey.
No, no, no, no, no.

16:05.573 --> 16:08.445
You get a beer on me.

16:08.532 --> 16:10.012
Thank you.

16:10.099 --> 16:14.277
♪♪

16:14.364 --> 16:17.063
[Woman laughing]

16:17.150 --> 16:22.416
♪♪

16:22.503 --> 16:24.461
Oh!
Oh, no!

16:28.248 --> 16:32.382
♪

16:32.469 --> 16:34.036
Morning, Dad.

16:34.080 --> 16:36.212
[Yawns]

16:36.299 --> 16:39.563
It's funny, I don't remember
ordering a boiled ham.

16:39.650 --> 16:43.872
Dad, this is my brand-new,
kick-ass indoor hot tub.

16:43.959 --> 16:45.265
You want in on this?

16:45.352 --> 16:48.442
I'm not getting into a tub
with my grown son.

16:48.529 --> 16:52.054
That's residual priest
nervousness, if you ask me.

16:52.141 --> 16:54.317
Well, no one did.

16:54.404 --> 16:56.754
If I were up for it,
I'd give you a rare high five

16:56.841 --> 16:59.366
for giving that to Dad.

16:59.453 --> 17:00.541
But I can't.

17:00.584 --> 17:04.109
I'm simply too...bereft.

17:04.196 --> 17:06.025
You're bereft?

17:06.112 --> 17:07.635
In a hot tub?

17:07.722 --> 17:10.420
I know! I should be
out-of-my-gourd excited.

17:10.507 --> 17:15.034
But instead, I'm realizing
that hot tubbing alone is...

17:15.121 --> 17:16.731
Pretty sad.
Pretty sad.

17:16.818 --> 17:20.430
You know, I should have my
right-hand man in here with me,

17:20.517 --> 17:23.912
but, no, Neil is nowhere
to be found -- again.

17:23.954 --> 17:26.480
Yeah, he's been
very busy lately.

17:26.567 --> 17:28.525
I imagine this must be
what it's like

17:28.612 --> 17:30.614
to reach the top
of Everest alone.

17:30.701 --> 17:32.747
[Studio audience laughing]

17:32.834 --> 17:34.444
What does the beauty matter

17:34.488 --> 17:36.925
if there's no other soul
to share it with?

17:37.012 --> 17:38.622
[Studio audience laughing]

17:38.666 --> 17:40.363
It's like that time
I saw Steve Harvey

17:40.450 --> 17:41.756
and no one believed me.

17:41.843 --> 17:44.759
Hey, do, uh,

17:44.802 --> 17:47.718
you want to get in?

17:47.805 --> 17:50.330
Uh, no thank you.

17:50.417 --> 17:52.680
I'm gonna go see Diane.

17:52.767 --> 17:53.942
Ugh.
Of course.

17:54.029 --> 17:55.465
Everybody has somebody
to hang out with

17:55.552 --> 17:57.424
except for me!

17:57.511 --> 18:00.122
That's it, I have decided that
I'm gonna get everyone

18:00.166 --> 18:04.083
in my life to start showing up
for my big moment of triumph!

18:04.126 --> 18:07.173
It starts now!

18:07.216 --> 18:09.958
Isn't this when
you spring into action?

18:10.045 --> 18:11.220
Yeah, but I'm naked in here

18:11.307 --> 18:12.743
and Lorraine's
in the kitchen, so...

18:12.830 --> 18:15.311
[Studio audience laughing]

18:15.398 --> 18:21.839
♪♪

18:21.926 --> 18:24.103
Allison: Diane?

18:24.190 --> 18:27.628
Hey, D, you okay?

18:27.715 --> 18:29.238
Yeah! Sorry.
Yeah.

18:29.325 --> 18:30.935
I'm -- I'm fine.

18:31.022 --> 18:34.417
Oh! Uh, you --
you didn't need to do that.

18:34.504 --> 18:36.854
My treat.

18:36.941 --> 18:40.075
Oh...

18:40.162 --> 18:42.033
Why'd you order that?

18:42.121 --> 18:45.254
Uh, in here, I'm known
as "Mrs. Wild Dude,"

18:45.341 --> 18:47.996
so they give me
free beer.

18:48.083 --> 18:51.304
So, that's the sudden urge
to take me day-drinkin'?

18:51.391 --> 18:53.175
'Cause you get free beer?No.

18:53.219 --> 18:55.612
It's 'cause I haven't
seen you lately.

18:55.699 --> 18:58.485
I guess.

18:58.572 --> 19:01.923
Do you wanna maybe tell me
why that is?

19:02.010 --> 19:04.012
We've both been busy.

19:04.099 --> 19:08.016
I think you've been busier
than I have.

19:08.059 --> 19:10.453
With Neil.

19:10.540 --> 19:12.977
I saw you here
the other night.

19:13.064 --> 19:14.762
Okay.
So?

19:14.849 --> 19:17.199
Well, you're cheating
on Chuck with Neil.

19:17.286 --> 19:18.679
Neil is...

19:18.722 --> 19:20.898
I don't know.

19:20.985 --> 19:23.379
Something
to look forward to.

19:23.466 --> 19:24.946
But are you happy?

19:25.033 --> 19:28.515
I'm not in love
or anything.

19:28.602 --> 19:30.952
I'm satisfied, hmm?

19:31.039 --> 19:34.042
And you deserve
to be satisfied.

19:34.129 --> 19:35.870
More than satisfied.

19:38.568 --> 19:41.484
Just be careful.

19:41.571 --> 19:43.225
Of what?!

19:43.312 --> 19:46.359
I'm pretty sure Neil's exacy
who I think he is, okay?

19:46.446 --> 19:48.361
That is the appeal.Yeah.

19:48.448 --> 19:51.059
I used to think so, too,
but, um...

19:54.236 --> 19:56.195
"But, um" what?

19:56.282 --> 19:59.720
I just want you
to be okay.

19:59.763 --> 20:00.938
I'm here.

20:01.025 --> 20:03.550
Okay.

20:03.637 --> 20:07.858
But Allison, he's, uh --
he's been here.

20:07.945 --> 20:10.252
It's not a lot,

20:10.296 --> 20:12.080
but it's somethin'.

20:16.650 --> 20:18.042
Enjoy your free beer.

20:26.442 --> 20:28.705
♪ The sex and music

20:28.792 --> 20:32.927
♪ Can align your mind ♪

20:33.014 --> 20:36.583
♪ Make the mood so right ♪

20:36.670 --> 20:40.587
♪ Our bodies moving,
rhythmically ♪

20:40.630 --> 20:42.066
♪ In time

20:42.153 --> 20:43.416
♪ Take it slow ♪

20:43.503 --> 20:46.767
♪ We've got all night ♪

20:46.810 --> 20:49.291
♪ Lay back, relax

20:49.378 --> 20:51.902
♪ Takin' it smooth ♪

20:51.989 --> 20:54.775
♪ Let's just kick back ♪

20:54.818 --> 20:57.038
♪ And give me you

20:57.125 --> 20:59.736
♪ Lay back, relax ♪

20:59.823 --> 21:01.521
[Exhales]

21:01.608 --> 21:04.175
[Electrical buzzing,
footsteps crunching]

21:04.263 --> 21:09.268
♪♪

21:09.355 --> 21:13.750
[Traffic passing]

21:13.837 --> 21:16.579
[Sighs]

21:16.666 --> 21:19.190
[Scoffs]

21:19.278 --> 21:28.330
♪♪

21:28.417 --> 21:30.376
Are you still
hungover?

21:30.463 --> 21:32.291
It's been, like, two days.Mnh-mm.

21:34.858 --> 21:36.556
It's food poisoning.

21:36.643 --> 21:39.689
Yeah, what did you eat?

21:39.776 --> 21:42.997
Brown liquors.

21:43.084 --> 21:44.825
Ow.Uh...

21:44.912 --> 21:48.002
is that why
you haven't packed yet?

21:48.089 --> 21:49.220
Mm.
Tammy.

21:49.308 --> 21:51.179
Okay.

21:51.266 --> 21:52.789
Um...

21:52.876 --> 21:56.793
I'm only gonna
ask this one --

21:56.880 --> 21:58.578
I shouldn't read
into this, right?

21:58.665 --> 22:01.363
Absolutely not.

22:01.407 --> 22:03.017
No.

22:03.104 --> 22:06.499
There's a box right over there.

22:06.586 --> 22:09.066
There's, like,
four cassette tapes in there.

22:09.153 --> 22:11.025
'Cause I wanna bring those.

22:11.068 --> 22:13.157
[Chuckles, winces]

22:13.244 --> 22:16.857
I guess it wouldn't be you if we
were moving on this any faster.

22:16.900 --> 22:19.816
Thank you...
I think.

22:19.903 --> 22:21.078
[Gasps]

22:21.122 --> 22:25.082
I just gotta go throw up
one more time.

22:25.169 --> 22:26.649
Sorry.

22:26.736 --> 22:28.564
[Rapid knocking]

22:28.651 --> 22:30.653
Leave me alone, Patty.

22:30.740 --> 22:33.395
[Knocking]

22:33.439 --> 22:35.136
[Exasperated sigh]

22:39.445 --> 22:41.882
What --Diane?

22:41.969 --> 22:44.754
Well, you're not dead
on the roadside.

22:44.798 --> 22:46.582
That's good, I guess.

22:46.626 --> 22:49.629
Oh, man, we were -- we were
supposed to hang out last night.

22:49.716 --> 22:53.284
I-I...
I totally spaced.

22:53.372 --> 22:54.851
Bullshit.

22:54.938 --> 22:56.897
[Sighs]

22:56.984 --> 22:59.160
Kevin called.

22:59.247 --> 23:00.770
There was this whole
hot tub thing,

23:00.857 --> 23:02.642
a-and he got mad at me,
and I just --

23:02.729 --> 23:04.208
I got distracted.

23:04.295 --> 23:05.732
[Scoffs]

23:05.819 --> 23:09.039
I -- He pointed out I've been
MIA a lot lately, and --

23:09.126 --> 23:10.389
and I think
he's right, you know?

23:10.476 --> 23:12.478
I've been spending way too
much time on --

23:12.565 --> 23:15.089
on other stuff.

23:15.132 --> 23:16.960
But you hate Kevin.

23:17.047 --> 23:18.571
What?

23:18.658 --> 23:21.182
No, Kevin's my best friend.

23:21.269 --> 23:22.705
He --
He looks out for me,

23:22.792 --> 23:24.838
and I've been really
shitty to him lately.

23:24.925 --> 23:30.234
Okay. Is that true, or is that
just what he tells you?

23:30.321 --> 23:32.585
No. No!
No, this is my fault,

23:32.672 --> 23:34.282
and it's 'cause of us
that I've been acting shitty.

23:34.369 --> 23:36.327
This whole thing is weird
and stupid.

23:36.371 --> 23:39.026
Having sex with me
is weird and stupid?

23:39.113 --> 23:41.507
Well, yeah!
Kinda!

23:44.161 --> 23:45.511
Okay.I --

23:45.598 --> 23:47.948
You really don't need
to worry about that anymore.

23:47.991 --> 23:49.602
I --

23:49.689 --> 23:51.908
[Sighs]

23:51.995 --> 23:53.867
[Door opens, closes]

23:53.954 --> 23:57.436
Hey, Diane --
alcoholic.

23:57.523 --> 24:00.177
All: Hi, Diane.

24:00.264 --> 24:02.179
I know you say you're not
supposed to get

24:02.223 --> 24:05.487
in a relationship the first year
of doing this whole thing,

24:05.574 --> 24:09.926
but, uh, I -- I got sober
after I met this guy,

24:10.013 --> 24:11.798
so I thought it didn't count.

24:13.539 --> 24:18.152
But it's over,
and okay, I get it.

24:18.239 --> 24:20.720
Because, like,

24:20.807 --> 24:24.027
I was able to get sober
because of him.

24:24.114 --> 24:26.508
Like, I had something
to look forward to

24:26.595 --> 24:30.991
that wasn't a nip of Fireball
after work...

24:31.078 --> 24:34.864
or during work.
[Scoffs]

24:34.951 --> 24:40.043
Without him -- I'm gonna be
honest with you, okay?

24:40.130 --> 24:42.132
Without him, I don't --
I don't know how long

24:42.219 --> 24:45.309
I can go without drinking.

24:45.396 --> 24:47.181
And without me...

24:49.879 --> 24:53.143
I don't want to have to worry
about him,

24:53.230 --> 24:55.798
but I can't stop
worrying about him.

24:56.364 --> 24:57.800
[Bottle smashes]

24:57.887 --> 24:59.541
[Exhales]

24:59.628 --> 25:02.718
♪♪

25:02.805 --> 25:04.328
I'm back, buddy!

25:04.415 --> 25:08.594
♪♪

25:12.554 --> 25:17.124
♪

25:17.211 --> 25:19.605
Neil! It's been a while
since I woke up

25:19.692 --> 25:21.607
to find you drinking
in our living room.

25:21.650 --> 25:24.697
Uh, I wouldn't call it
our living room.

25:24.784 --> 25:26.916
You're about as welcome here
as a book,

25:26.960 --> 25:28.918
in that I feel dumb and mad
when I see you,

25:29.005 --> 25:31.530
and I don't care at all
what's going on inside of you.

25:31.617 --> 25:34.228
[Studio audience laughing]

25:34.315 --> 25:36.143
Ah!
Neil!

25:36.230 --> 25:38.014
It's good to see you back
where you belong.

25:38.101 --> 25:40.190
Yeah.
Two peas in a pod.

25:40.277 --> 25:42.279
Like Tom Brady and --Gronk?

25:42.366 --> 25:45.761
You definitely have
the same IQ.

25:45.805 --> 25:47.371
Thank you.

25:47.458 --> 25:49.765
It just feels right to have
you next to me, buddy.

25:49.852 --> 25:52.115
Especially since we're getting
ready for our annual

25:52.202 --> 25:54.378
Tour de Franzia
bar crawl!

25:54.465 --> 25:56.816
Ah, yes.
Your annual drunken race.

25:56.903 --> 26:01.603
Tiny little tricycles,
and great big boxes of wine.

26:01.690 --> 26:04.127
And a trophy!
The boys from Maloney's

26:04.214 --> 26:06.652
don't stand a chance.

26:06.739 --> 26:09.785
And do you remember
why you lost last year?

26:09.872 --> 26:12.222
I got my stomach pumped.Of course.

26:12.309 --> 26:15.356
Everyone else calls it
"you puked all over my kitchen."

26:15.443 --> 26:17.401
[Studio audience laughing]

26:17.488 --> 26:19.621
We all lost
that day.

26:19.665 --> 26:21.101
We sure did.

26:21.188 --> 26:23.712
Amen.Amen.

26:23.799 --> 26:26.497
How much has changed
since I've been gone?

26:26.585 --> 26:28.151
Well, good luck.

26:28.238 --> 26:29.675
And Neil, maybe this year,

26:29.718 --> 26:31.546
you can puke all over
your own kitchen.

26:31.633 --> 26:35.115
[Studio audience laughing]

26:35.202 --> 26:37.813
Joke's on her, my kitchen's
already covered in puke.

26:37.900 --> 26:40.337
[Studio audience laughing]

26:40.424 --> 26:48.345
♪♪

26:48.432 --> 26:56.310
♪♪

26:56.397 --> 26:57.572
Yeah.

27:11.238 --> 27:12.631
Mm.

27:16.373 --> 27:18.462
[Clattering]

27:18.549 --> 27:23.511
[Footsteps creaking,
crashing]

27:23.554 --> 27:26.079
[Sighs]
Neil.

27:29.125 --> 27:30.692
Neil?

27:30.779 --> 27:33.042
Oh...

27:33.129 --> 27:36.089
Neil!

27:36.176 --> 27:38.004
Oh, please,
just let yourself in.

27:38.091 --> 27:40.615
Well, I pay the mortgage,
so, yeah,

27:40.702 --> 27:43.966
ugh, I will
let myself in.

27:49.450 --> 27:50.973
How much wine have you had?

27:51.060 --> 27:53.062
[Scoffs]

27:53.149 --> 27:55.891
Here.

27:55.935 --> 27:57.676
I'm fine.

28:00.766 --> 28:02.768
[Groans]
I gotta go.

28:02.855 --> 28:04.378
You're not going
anywhere, Neil.

28:04.421 --> 28:06.380
I have to!

28:06.467 --> 28:08.861
We lost the crawl
and Kevin's pissed.

28:08.904 --> 28:11.341
Those guys from
Maloney's cheated,

28:11.428 --> 28:13.387
and now we gotta get 'em back.

28:13.474 --> 28:16.216
I just need to go to
the paint store

28:16.303 --> 28:17.652
and find that goat.

28:17.739 --> 28:18.914
Goat?Mm.

28:19.001 --> 28:21.090
You sound like an idiot.

28:21.134 --> 28:22.439
Why don't you just sleep
this one off?

28:22.483 --> 28:24.137
God, will you just
move out already?

28:24.224 --> 28:27.183
I will!
I am!

28:27.270 --> 28:28.794
No, you shut up.

28:28.881 --> 28:31.274
Just lie down.

28:31.361 --> 28:33.276
Kevin needs me.

28:33.320 --> 28:34.408
Kevin will be fine.

28:34.495 --> 28:36.323
Kevin's always fine.

28:41.458 --> 28:43.809
[Door opens, closes]

28:43.896 --> 28:48.596
♪♪

28:48.683 --> 28:50.119
Shit.

28:50.206 --> 28:53.079
♪♪

28:53.166 --> 28:55.821
Hey, do you have any more shifts
I can pick up?

28:57.823 --> 29:00.477
Sam?

29:00.521 --> 29:04.525
Jenn's parents are trying to
claim sole ownership of Bev's.

29:04.612 --> 29:07.746
What?!

29:07.833 --> 29:11.184
Jenn told them we split --
and probably why we split --

29:11.271 --> 29:12.751
and...

29:12.838 --> 29:15.623
they're taking it.

29:15.666 --> 29:16.929
But --
[Scoffs]

29:17.016 --> 29:20.106
Bev's is yours!
They can't do that.

29:20.193 --> 29:21.977
Well, the way I let them
structure it,

29:22.064 --> 29:24.806
I think they can.

29:24.893 --> 29:28.027
So sorry.

29:28.114 --> 29:29.985
Still feel grateful
to Kevin now?

29:30.072 --> 29:31.857
[Chuckles]
Yeah.

29:31.944 --> 29:33.902
I don't think he blew up
my life on purpose,

29:33.989 --> 29:36.644
but it's like
that makes it worse.

29:37.906 --> 29:41.867
If only he'd accidentally
fix it somehow.

29:41.954 --> 29:43.607
Uh, A-Allison?

29:43.694 --> 29:44.652
Got a sec?

29:44.739 --> 29:46.001
Oh.
Yeah.

29:46.088 --> 29:48.308
Um...
Back room.

29:56.795 --> 29:58.797
Ugh. God.

29:58.884 --> 30:00.363
This is sad.

30:00.450 --> 30:03.671
If I ever wind up living
in the packie, kill me.

30:03.714 --> 30:05.673
Well, I'm really glad
you came by.

30:05.716 --> 30:09.198
I hate
where we left off.

30:09.242 --> 30:10.765
But you could've come
by the house.

30:10.852 --> 30:12.288
Uh, no.
I couldn't.

30:12.375 --> 30:14.551
Not for this.

30:14.595 --> 30:17.816
It is what it is, and I don't
want to hear about it.

30:19.948 --> 30:23.212
About what?

30:23.299 --> 30:25.388
Diane, what is this?

30:25.475 --> 30:28.217
I won it playing Keno
a few weeks back.

30:28.304 --> 30:30.480
Thought you could, uh,
use a little extra cash

30:30.567 --> 30:33.179
for your...
vacation.

30:37.052 --> 30:40.403
Diane, I --
I don't deserve this.

30:40.447 --> 30:42.362
You were right, what you said,
I've been distracted

30:42.449 --> 30:44.103
by my own bullshit,

30:44.190 --> 30:47.062
and -- and you
need to take this.

30:47.106 --> 30:48.498
And use it for what?

30:48.585 --> 30:50.022
[Scoffs]

30:50.109 --> 30:52.328
I thought about hitting
Atlantic City with Neil,

30:52.415 --> 30:54.374
but that's not gonna happen.

30:56.463 --> 31:00.510
Diane, I was never rootin'
for you to be unhappy.

31:00.597 --> 31:02.991
I just wanted you
to have more.

31:06.429 --> 31:09.693
You know,
I never wanted kids.

31:09.780 --> 31:11.521
I thought I'd always have boys,

31:11.608 --> 31:14.829
and then I would have to take
care of them all until I died.

31:16.613 --> 31:19.573
And I felt like
I already had a girl.

31:22.271 --> 31:23.969
Thank you.

31:28.147 --> 31:29.757
Thank Kevin, hmm?

31:29.844 --> 31:31.585
If it weren't for him, I'd be
blowing it on roulette

31:31.628 --> 31:33.500
with Neil.

31:35.850 --> 31:44.990
♪

31:45.033 --> 31:48.254
I told you you could
always get more money.

31:48.341 --> 31:49.690
God, I wish
I had your luck.

31:49.777 --> 31:52.171
Well, this wasn't luck.

31:55.783 --> 31:58.917
Sam, I really -- I want to
help you keep this place.

31:58.960 --> 32:01.310
Yeah, that's --
that's nice,

32:01.397 --> 32:04.270
but Jenn's parents
are ruthless.

32:04.357 --> 32:06.446
This isn't about money
for them.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.319
So, how?

32:10.406 --> 32:12.452
I have no idea.

32:15.020 --> 32:16.673
I think Kevin might?

32:16.760 --> 32:19.633
♪♪

32:19.720 --> 32:23.289
[Knocking]
Come on, guys!

32:23.332 --> 32:24.812
Ugh!

32:24.899 --> 32:26.901
Pete! Anybody!

32:26.988 --> 32:29.251
Patty?

32:29.338 --> 32:31.862
What's going on?

32:31.950 --> 32:34.517
Neil got drunk on red wine,

32:34.561 --> 32:36.345
and when he's wine drunk,

32:36.432 --> 32:38.521
well, he's a lot like
my dad.

32:38.608 --> 32:40.306
I tried to keep him
in the apartment,

32:40.393 --> 32:44.658
but he and Kevin wanted
to do something stupid.

32:44.745 --> 32:48.096
Oh. And the car's gone, so
whatever Kevin wanted to do,

32:48.183 --> 32:50.403
they are doing.

32:50.490 --> 32:51.970
And they drove.

32:52.057 --> 32:53.275
Fantastic.

32:53.362 --> 32:56.844
Want me to come over
and wait up with you?

32:59.238 --> 33:01.327
I should probably pack.

33:01.414 --> 33:03.198
Yeah, I -- Yeah.

33:03.285 --> 33:07.898
Few things I need
to figure out, too.

33:07.986 --> 33:09.683
Well...

33:12.381 --> 33:14.775
I should have gone
to nursing school.

33:16.777 --> 33:18.474
You would've had to work
on your bedside manner.

33:18.561 --> 33:20.824
Shut up!

33:20.911 --> 33:23.218
Oh.
Yeah.

33:23.262 --> 33:25.133
Okay.

33:25.220 --> 33:28.006
But I-I still think that
I'd be great at it.

33:28.093 --> 33:29.703
I do, too.

33:29.746 --> 33:32.140
So, prove it!

33:33.750 --> 33:37.145
Okay.
The back ones?

33:37.232 --> 33:40.061
Well, not the front ones!

33:40.105 --> 33:42.020
We need two or three.

33:42.107 --> 33:45.762
Jesus.
Open up.

33:45.849 --> 33:47.590
Oh, that's a very good one.Ah.

33:47.677 --> 33:49.027
Okay, on the count of three.Uh-huh.

33:49.114 --> 33:50.376
One...Uh-huh!

33:50.419 --> 33:51.899
Two -- wait.

33:51.942 --> 33:55.511
Wait.
Why are we doing this again?

33:55.598 --> 33:57.383
Dental records.Sure.

33:57.426 --> 34:00.951
You said that, but why do
we need dental records?

34:01.039 --> 34:03.084
Because Sam keeps
giving me a hard time

34:03.128 --> 34:04.912
about how
I'm gonna kill myself,

34:04.955 --> 34:07.784
so I figure
I torch Kevin's car,

34:07.871 --> 34:10.483
I sprinkle a few teeth
in the front seat,

34:10.570 --> 34:12.179
it looks like
I burn up in there,

34:12.266 --> 34:15.574
and then they identify me
by my dental records.

34:15.661 --> 34:17.098
So, Bob's your uncle.

34:17.141 --> 34:19.534
[Laughing]

34:19.621 --> 34:25.150
[Both laughing]

34:25.237 --> 34:26.934
What?

34:28.978 --> 34:32.853
That's an awful plan!

34:32.940 --> 34:35.246
Why?Well...

34:35.333 --> 34:40.774
It's just not at all
how dental records...work.

34:40.817 --> 34:42.471
Or fires.

34:42.558 --> 34:44.125
Okay, well, I need
to figure something out,

34:44.212 --> 34:46.170
'cause this is the last thing
I need to do.

34:46.257 --> 34:48.389
Mm.

34:48.476 --> 34:50.391
The last thing.Yeah.

34:50.478 --> 34:53.134
So, I have to be smart about it.

34:53.178 --> 34:57.312
Yeah -- pliers notwithstanding,
I guess.

34:57.399 --> 34:59.880
Sam thinks I'm stalling.

34:59.967 --> 35:02.578
Okay, what is with
everyone

35:02.665 --> 35:04.798
rushing everybody
all the time.

35:04.841 --> 35:06.278
Thank you!

35:06.365 --> 35:08.584
Nick is in a coma.

35:08.671 --> 35:11.196
Kevin and Neil
are back to normal.

35:11.283 --> 35:13.241
So, I --
I do have time.

35:13.328 --> 35:15.113
I can't be stupid
about this.

35:15.200 --> 35:17.506
Mm. You gotta
think things through.

35:17.593 --> 35:19.595
Yeah.

35:19.682 --> 35:21.467
You gotta be sure.

35:24.731 --> 35:26.820
How do you know
when you're sure?

35:30.040 --> 35:32.826
[Cellphone vibrating]

35:32.869 --> 35:36.656
Oh.
It's Tammy.

35:36.743 --> 35:38.353
Well, I should probab--
I --

35:38.397 --> 35:39.789
Okay.

35:39.876 --> 35:42.009
[Clears throat]

35:42.096 --> 35:44.185
Hey.

35:44.229 --> 35:45.752
Oh, sorry.

35:45.795 --> 35:48.537
Officer. Yeah, I -- I thought
you were somebody else.

35:48.581 --> 35:50.409
How can I help you?

35:54.108 --> 35:56.154
Yeah.

35:56.241 --> 35:57.807
I'm his sister.

35:57.894 --> 36:00.506
[Breathing deeply]

36:00.549 --> 36:02.943
Man: O'Connor?

36:03.030 --> 36:03.987
You made bail.

36:04.074 --> 36:11.256
♪♪

36:23.398 --> 36:25.531
[Inhales sharply]

36:28.098 --> 36:29.883
Thank you.

36:32.277 --> 36:33.887
You okay?

36:36.411 --> 36:38.065
No.

36:48.989 --> 36:52.949
♪

36:53.036 --> 36:54.473
[Yawning]

36:54.560 --> 36:56.562
You woke up!
Another win.

36:56.649 --> 36:58.781
[Studio audience laughing]

36:58.868 --> 37:00.827
Eh.

37:00.914 --> 37:04.047
Mornin'.

37:04.134 --> 37:04.961
What is this?

37:05.048 --> 37:07.442
It's called breakfast, Dad.

37:07.486 --> 37:09.270
I know it's breakfast.

37:09.357 --> 37:11.881
But where are the meats?

37:11.968 --> 37:15.363
He's right!
Allison, what is happening here?

37:15.450 --> 37:17.235
Yes, I left out the meats.

37:17.322 --> 37:20.150
I hate it, too, but we have to
cut back a little bit,

37:20.194 --> 37:22.936
because I'm losing my job
at the diner.

37:23.023 --> 37:24.677
What?
What'd you do?

37:24.764 --> 37:26.766
Sam's in-laws are coming
after the diner in the divorce

37:26.853 --> 37:28.158
and they're closing it down.

37:28.202 --> 37:29.551
Of course he can't keep
his restaurant.

37:29.638 --> 37:32.119
He can't even keep
his own wife!

37:32.206 --> 37:35.862
Well, we just have to cut back
on a few things, alright?

37:35.949 --> 37:37.080
Breakfast meats,

37:37.167 --> 37:38.865
maybe buy
a little less beer.

37:38.952 --> 37:42.216
[Grunts]
Excuse me?

37:42.303 --> 37:44.000
A-And what are you giving up?

37:44.087 --> 37:45.741
Well, we can stop ordering
takeout all the time.

37:45.828 --> 37:49.832
Meaning,
you'll...cook?

37:49.876 --> 37:52.748
Um, I can boil a dinner
with the best of them.

37:52.792 --> 37:55.795
[Both shudder]

37:55.882 --> 37:57.318
Well, if you have such a problem
with it,

37:57.362 --> 37:58.928
you can take it up with Sam

37:59.015 --> 38:01.670
and his terrible
divorce settlement.

38:01.714 --> 38:03.281
Actually, you know what?
Don't do that,

38:03.368 --> 38:05.544
because he doesn't enjoy
talking to you.

38:05.587 --> 38:08.286
[Studio audience laughing,
playful sitcom music]

38:13.552 --> 38:17.207
Do you think
he's still in jail?

38:17.251 --> 38:19.645
Well, Kevin definitely
didn't bail him out.

38:21.864 --> 38:23.649
I should've.

38:23.736 --> 38:25.651
Oh, 'cause you're worried about
him getting back at us,

38:25.738 --> 38:29.307
or you're worried
about him?

38:29.394 --> 38:31.613
Yes.

38:31.700 --> 38:33.485
It's good that you didn't.

38:33.572 --> 38:36.183
Okay, just let him dry out
in there for the weekend,

38:36.270 --> 38:38.664
let him take care
of himself for once.

38:40.579 --> 38:42.668
Ah!
Ouch.

38:42.755 --> 38:45.453
[Chuckling]

38:45.540 --> 38:48.064
Want me to make you
some soup or something?

38:48.108 --> 38:49.762
Curry's good for
a hangover.

38:49.849 --> 38:52.417
Better than --
Better than hazelnut coffee.

38:52.504 --> 38:54.680
We had the same amount.

38:54.767 --> 38:58.466
It's really almost rude
that you feel absolutely fine.

38:58.553 --> 39:00.250
Kevin's rubbing off on me.

39:00.338 --> 39:05.038
Meanwhile, this has been my
second hangover of this week.

39:05.125 --> 39:07.170
Tammy's not gonna love it.

39:09.564 --> 39:13.089
She thinks you're
a bad influence on me.

39:13.176 --> 39:15.353
Bad influence?

39:15.440 --> 39:18.356
She told me about
your thing with Sam.

39:18.443 --> 39:20.793
As if that's the thing that
makes you morally compromised.

39:20.880 --> 39:23.404
She told you that?I already knew.

39:23.448 --> 39:26.189
Yeah, but she didn't know
that you knew.

39:26.276 --> 39:29.062
She's just jealous.

39:29.105 --> 39:31.238
She'll get over it.

39:31.325 --> 39:34.067
'Cause we're friends?

39:34.154 --> 39:35.851
Yeah.

39:37.984 --> 39:41.248
And you're not gonna be around
for much longer.

39:41.335 --> 39:44.817
Hey.
Oh, hey.

39:46.819 --> 39:49.735
I'm only slightly hungover
this time, I swear.

39:49.822 --> 39:51.389
What is that smell?

39:51.476 --> 39:52.781
You got a Yankee Candle going?

39:52.825 --> 39:55.001
Hazelnut.
Sorry.

39:55.088 --> 39:57.395
I'm gonna get out of here,
but feel better.

39:59.309 --> 40:01.094
Bye.

40:07.317 --> 40:09.537
Hey, hold on.

40:09.624 --> 40:11.321
We gotta talk.

40:11.409 --> 40:13.454
Look, I know what you said
about us hanging out,

40:13.541 --> 40:16.109
but you can't control her life,
we're friends.

40:16.152 --> 40:18.459
That's not what this is, okay?

40:18.546 --> 40:20.940
I'm worried about her.

40:21.027 --> 40:22.768
Worried how?

40:24.813 --> 40:26.511
This is Patty at a gas station
in Vermont,

40:26.598 --> 40:28.338
where I'm pretty sure
she assaulted a trucker

40:28.426 --> 40:30.297
for some pills,

40:30.384 --> 40:32.604
pills that ended up on the y
that broke into your house.

40:34.388 --> 40:36.172
I don't know exactly
what it means,

40:36.216 --> 40:38.784
but I know she's wrapped upn
something stupid,

40:38.827 --> 40:40.873
something bad.

40:40.960 --> 40:45.660
Oh, uh, have you shown this
to anyone else?

40:45.747 --> 40:47.053
No.

40:47.140 --> 40:49.272
The minute I do,
it becomes official.

40:49.359 --> 40:54.364
Okay. Well, uh, there must be
some misunderstanding.

40:54.408 --> 40:57.455
That's not like Patty.
You know her.

40:57.542 --> 40:59.979
I mean, I think I do,
but don't you think

41:00.066 --> 41:02.024
she's been acting weird lately?

41:02.111 --> 41:03.635
Mm, no.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.332
No, no.
I mean, not at all.

41:05.419 --> 41:09.075
She's been -- she's been
completely normal with me.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.603
What?

41:15.690 --> 41:18.345
Nothing.

41:18.432 --> 41:21.566
Bye, Allison.

41:21.653 --> 41:22.871
Bye.

41:22.958 --> 41:30.052
♪♪

41:30.139 --> 41:37.320
♪♪

41:37.407 --> 41:38.626
[Grunts]

41:38.713 --> 41:40.323
Patty, what the hell
are you doing?!

41:40.410 --> 41:42.021
Honey, that wasn't the guy.

41:42.108 --> 41:43.675
[Man groaning]

41:43.718 --> 41:46.199
[Pills rattling]

41:46.286 --> 41:48.984
[Screaming]

41:49.071 --> 41:52.988
♪♪

41:53.075 --> 41:54.512
Man [echoing]: Allison?

41:56.644 --> 41:59.429
Allison?Yeah? Yeah?

41:59.473 --> 42:01.823
Jenn's parents dropped
their claim on the diner.

42:03.564 --> 42:05.087
They did?Yeah, yeah.

42:05.174 --> 42:08.308
They were informed of an
impending personal injury suit

42:08.395 --> 42:10.789
against the diner,
a slip and fall.

42:10.876 --> 42:12.921
If we lost, they'd be on
the hook for the payout,

42:13.008 --> 42:15.533
and they wanted
no part of it.

42:15.620 --> 42:18.361
How did that happen?

42:18.448 --> 42:19.972
Was it --

42:20.059 --> 42:24.367
The plaintiff's name was
"Kelvin McLoberts."

42:24.454 --> 42:27.066
[Chuckling]

42:27.109 --> 42:29.155
Yeah.
This all feels a little slimy,

42:29.242 --> 42:31.766
but I guess technically,
I didn't do anything,

42:31.853 --> 42:36.641
so, I mean, I can just
let this happen, right?

42:39.644 --> 42:41.428
Sam, I don't want to leave.

42:45.258 --> 42:47.739
After all the --Yeah.

42:47.826 --> 42:50.263
But why?I'm just...

42:50.306 --> 42:52.744
not ready to give up...

42:52.831 --> 42:54.484
everything.

42:54.572 --> 42:56.269
You were right.
I was stalling.

42:56.356 --> 42:58.837
And I thought I could.
I thought I had time.

42:58.924 --> 43:02.144
But now Tammy's found...
something,

43:02.231 --> 43:05.800
and soon, she's just
gonna ruin all of it.

43:05.887 --> 43:09.021
Ruin what?
Your great life here?

43:10.849 --> 43:13.503
Yeah.What?!

43:13.591 --> 43:14.983
I know! I know.
It's just that,

43:15.070 --> 43:17.725
everything's
been easier lately.

43:17.812 --> 43:20.510
But Kevin --Yeah, it turns out,

43:20.554 --> 43:23.078
if you make your problems
Kevin's problems,

43:23.165 --> 43:26.865
he just
fixes all of them.

43:26.952 --> 43:30.695
Look, he has taken from me
for 15 years.

43:30.782 --> 43:34.307
I'm just starting
to get something back.

43:34.394 --> 43:36.135
I don't want you to leave,
either,

43:36.222 --> 43:38.398
but you kinda
have to, right?

43:38.485 --> 43:41.227
I mean, Tammy --She is a problem.

43:43.011 --> 43:45.927
But now I know how to take
care of my problems.

43:48.060 --> 43:49.714
I introduce them
to Kevin.

43:53.369 --> 43:55.371
Hey.

43:55.458 --> 43:56.764
Wanna hear a crazy story?

43:58.505 --> 44:01.682
Allison, if Kevin decided
Tammy's a problem,

44:01.769 --> 44:03.205
she won't be a cop
in three days.

44:03.249 --> 44:07.993
Neil kept talking about
this crazy story he had.

44:08.080 --> 44:09.864
It was really awful.

44:09.908 --> 44:11.474
Patty: What?

44:11.561 --> 44:14.303
Patty, uh, I have to go
find Neil.

44:14.390 --> 44:16.262
Have you seen him lately?

44:16.349 --> 44:17.785
Patty's getting worried.

44:17.872 --> 44:18.830
Neil?

44:23.878 --> 44:33.496
♪

44:33.583 --> 44:43.332
♪♪

44:43.419 --> 44:51.514
♪♪
